{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_parsifal_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608671/1957122601/0672.xml":{"full_text":"THE EVENING\u2019STAR, Washington, D. C.\nminaDAT. pycember m. iwt\nB-14\n\"Business\nU. S. May Want to Peek\nInto Your Pocketbook\nBy DONALD B. HADLEY\nA number of Washington irn consumer* will be asked\nto let the Government take a look on the Inside of their\npocketbook* to see where the money went and what will be\nleft to buy things in 1958\nThe income tax collector will not get any help because\nthe information ia to be strictly confidential, but the Federal\nReserve Board is trying to get\ndown-to-earth information on\nwhat the business outlook is.\nThe board apparently feels\none of the best ways is to take\na look into the consumer\u2019s\npocketbook and discover how.\nthe family budget is faring.\nIts 13th annual survey of\nconsumer finance will be con\nducted in January and Feb\nruary in 69 representative areas\nof the Nation, and the Wash\nington Metropolitan Area is\none of them.\nThe Survey Research Center;\nof the University of Michigan\nwill carry out the interviews\nwith consumers, whose ad-,\ndresses will be picked at ran\ndom.\nResults will be taken as rep\nresentative of national con\nditions and will be used in\nevaluating policies not only\nof the board but of other Gov\nernment agencies and private\norganizations.\nInterviewers WiU Ask\n1958 Buying Intentions\nThe 1958 survey will include\nquestions regarding income,\nfinancial position, major pur\nchases in 1957 and intentions\nto buy cars, other durable goods\nand houses in 1958 Also cov\nered will be the consumer\u2019s\nevaluation of his current finan\ncial situation and his prospects\nfor 1958.\nAll interviews are held in the\nstrictest confidence and no in\nformation concerning individ\nual families is disclosed, the\nboard emphasized today in an\nnouncing plans for the survey.\nThe information is used\nsolely for statistical analysis i\nof the financial position and\nprospects of different groups\nof people in the country.\nListed among the areas to\nbe covered by the survey are j\nthe District of Columbia. Mont-\ngdmery and Prince Georges\nCounties in Maryland and\nFalls Church in Virginia.\nReal Estate Transfers\nTop 1958 in Naveasber\nWashington aeal estate ac- J\ntivity in November ran ahead!,\nof a year ago although first\nmortgage financing continued\nto lag. data from the Wash\nington Real Estate Board In\ndicated today.\nNew deeds representing prop\nerty transfers numbered 1.370\nin November, compared with i\n1.195 in the same 1956 month,\ndespite a decrease from 1,454\nin the previous month. In 11\nmonths this year, deeds totaled\n14,173. compared with 14.271 a\nyear earlier.\nDeeds of trust or first mort\ngages numbered 850 and i\namounted to $12,038,220 in No-;\nMUTUAL FUNDS\nNSW YORK. Dm 28 \u2014National\nAssociation Securities Dealers. Inc\nINoaa Qeolations\nBid Asked\nAberdeen Bund 14* I SO\nAffiliated Yt-nd Stu 5.72\nAm Business Shra 38* UHU\nAm Mutual Bund B#4 7,58\nAssoc fund Ttust 1C- 1.14\nAtom Dee Mutual 4 4 40.\nAse Houahton Yd A 4 73 5 14\nAse Houehton Yd B O lio ~28\nAse Houahton Stk Yd.. 323 IS i\nAse Science A II Klt* \u00bb73j\nBlue Rldae Mutual nan 10.74\nBoston And 14 wt 1# 17\nBroad Street Incest 18 4* 21.03\nBullock Yund 10 47 11.41 s\nCanada Gen Yund 10.33 11.17\nCanadian Yund 15.2* 18 5o\nCentury ahrs Trust 20 47 22 13\nChemical Fund 14 .hi* loon\nSomtritb Income Yd 705 788\nomwlth Investment 7K2 Ml\nCom with Stk Yund 11 00 11 Mi\nCons Invest Trust IS 2* I*.7*\nde veth Mut Yund 01 no 04 40\nDelaware Yund A*7 \u00bb42\nevert Orowth Stk *do dl 4\nvers Invest Yund 7.22 1 91\nSvtdend Shares 1 23 d 258\nerf us Fund *4O 9.20\ntoft A How Bal 19 42 20 77\nBaton A How Stk 17 87 18 11\nElectronics mves 407 4 45\nFidelity Fund 11. an 12.541\nF. I. Y. 300 328\nFounders Mut Yund 8 80 j\nFundamental Invest 13 51 14 81\nGroup Sec Csp Orth 008 08*\nOrouo Bee Com Stork woo 10 5\" j\ngroup Sec Yuliy Adm 7*o I\nOroup Bee Indust